trailingComments.value: * * Divides a big endian number by a single limb number. * Can only work with limbs of size at most sqrt( 2^53 ). * Allows to prefix the dividend with an intermediate remainder. * * Does not update the remainder. * * Input * ----- * - 0 <= tmp <= d - 1 * - 1 <= d <= r - 1 * - |Q| = |D| * * @param {Number} r The radix. * @param {Number} tmp Intermediate remainder (MUST be < d). * @param {Number} d The divisor >= 1. * @param {Array} D The dividend (NOT modified). * @param {Number} Di Left of dividend. * @param {Number} Dj Right of dividend. * @param {Array} Q The quotient. * @param {Number} Qi Left of quotient.
